# Class: SubAgent

TypeScript SDK reference

[weave](/weave/reference/typescript-sdk) / SubAgent A nested agent invocation — used when the current agent hands work to another named agent (e.g. a planner calling a researcher). Emits an `invoke_agent` span tagged with the sub-agent’s name and (optionally) its model. Created by `weave.startSubagent()` (or `turn.startAgent()`, or `llm.startAgent()`) and terminated with `end()`. `Example`
    
    
    const sub = weave.startSubagent({name: 'researcher', model: 'gpt-4o'});
    try {
      // ... orchestrate the sub-agent's LLM/Tool calls ...
    } finally {
      sub.end();
    }
    

